news.title: Aurum PropTech to raise Rs 343 crore through rights issue
news.para: The company will issue 3 equity shares for every 2 shares held by the eligible shareholders as on the record date to be announced later.

news.title: Wave, 3C & Logix Group got 80% of business land in Noida, ran up Rs 14,000 crore dues: CAG
news.para: Of the total allotments made in 2005-2018, 79.8% of commercial land was allotted to these three companies, the auditor found, adding an examination revealed violations of terms and conditions by them with the acquiescence of Noida officials.

news.title: Noida's sports city caused loss of Rs 9,000 crore to exchequer: CAG report
news.para: CAG has stated in its report that land in the sectors earmarked for developing sports infrastructure, along with residential apartments, was allocated to provide undue benefits to the allottees, causing a loss of Rs 9,000 crore to Noida Authority.

news.title: CAG report: Why the housing dream turned sour for buyers in Noida
news.para: Out of a total 113 projects that were initiated in the period under audit (2005-06 to 2017-18), only 63% (71) were either completed or partially completed, the CAG said. And out of the 1.3 lakh sanctioned flats, occupancy certificates have been issued for just 44%.

news.title: CAG report: Bank guarantee clause scrapped by Noida CEO in 2006, then dues shot up
news.para: ​The dropping of this clause for an escrow account, meant to safeguard the interests of the Noida Authority against defaulting developers and allottees, led to dues piling up, the national auditor has said in the first comprehensive performance audit of the Noida Authority.

news.title: CAG slams 'irregularities' in Noida land allotments
news.para: The exchequer lost out on Rs 52,000 crore as officials in the New Okhla Industrial Development Authority (Noida) adopted dubious practices, turning Delhi's satellite town into a haven for real estate developers with just around 18% used for industrial development.

news.title: NBCC fined Rs 1 crore for violating construction ban at Netaji Shubhash Nagar
news.para: "On December 3 too, the National Buildings Construction Corporation (NBCC) was fined Rs 5 lakh for violating the ban at the same site. Now, we have received reports of construction being undertaken at the site at night," Rai said.

news.title: NOIDA allotted farmhouses in 'questionable' manner, loss of Rs 2,833 crore to exchequer: CAG
news.para: ​In the audit report tabled in the Uttar Pradesh Assembly on Friday, the Comptroller and Auditor General (CAG) also flagged significant lapses in policies adopted by the New Okhla Industrial Development Authority (NOIDA), also called the Noida Authority.

news.title: Shimao Group bonds jump on report it plans to repay debts
news.para: Bonds issued by Shanghai Shimao Co Ltd and Shanghai Shimao Construction Co Ltd, both owned by Shimao, were top gainers in Shanghai Stock Exchange's corporate bond market on Friday morning.

news.title: Chinese Estates Holdings shelves plans to go private
news.para: The company, which is the third-largest shareholder of Evergrande, received a proposal to be taken private from the British Virgin Islands-based company for HK$1.91 billion ($245.30 million) in early October.

news.title: US home construction rebounds a strong 11.8% in November
news.para: The double-digit percentage increase last month left home construction at a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.68 million units, an 8.3% increase from the rate at this time last year, the Commerce Department reported Thursday.

news.title: Shimao Group downgraded by Moody's, Fitch on increased financing risks
news.para: S&P downgraded China Evergrande Group to "selective default" on Friday, and Moody's and Fitch downgraded Guangzhou R&F Properties to Caa2 from B3, and C from B-, respectively.

news.title: Trichy: Experts to study TNUHDB site over plaints of substandard quality
news.para: ​​The Rs 12.50 crore project to build 192 dwelling units for urban poor is coming up in ward 15 of Trichy corporation at Kalmanthai in Tharanallur.

news.title: Lucknow development body eases norms for commercial status for houses
news.para: LDA secretary Pawan Kumar Gangwar said, "The authority will charge a certain fee from the private developers before issuing a licence to them to do the construction work of housing units.

news.title: North Delhi civic body plans to lease out commercial plots for revenue
news.para: According to the corporation, the 481-square-metre Naniwala Bagh commercial complex in Azadpur, with different sizes of plots, has been lying vacant for years. The civic body hopes to lease it out to a bidder for approximately Rs 12.2 crore.
